 50→/// Nudge sent to the model when auto-continue fires after it stopped mid-task
 51→/// without emitting a substantive final answer.
 52→///
 53→/// Deliberately avoids phrasing like "provide a brief final answer" because
 54→/// that invites the model to overwrite an already-emitted long response with
 55→/// a terse summary (see GH #628).
 56→const AUTO_CONTINUE_NUDGE: &str = "Your previous response ended without tool calls and without a final answer. \
 57→     If there are still steps to run, continue executing them. \
 58→     Otherwise reply with exactly: done";
 59→
 60→/// Minimum character count (after trimming) that qualifies an assistant text
 61→/// response as a "substantive final answer" — at or above this length the
 62→/// auto-continue nudge is suppressed because the model has clearly finished
 63→/// talking and nudging it risks losing the answer (GH #628).
 64→const AUTO_CONTINUE_SUBSTANTIVE_TEXT_THRESHOLD: usize = 40;
