 44→/// Wrapper around `LlamaBackend` that opts into `Send + Sync`.
 45→///
 46→/// `LlamaBackend` is `!Send` because `llama-cpp-2` doesn't mark its FFI
 47→/// handle as thread-safe. In practice the backend is an opaque init token
 48→/// with no mutable state after construction, so sharing across threads is
 49→/// safe. Wrapping it in a newtype keeps the `unsafe` declaration localised.
 50→struct SendSyncBackend(LlamaBackend);
 51→
 52→// SAFETY: LlamaBackend is an immutable init handle with no thread-local state.
 53→#[allow(unsafe_code)]
 54→unsafe impl Send for SendSyncBackend {}
 55→#[allow(unsafe_code)]
 56→unsafe impl Sync for SendSyncBackend {}
